                <td bgcolor="#333366" valign="top"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/27/2002&nbsp;: 04:28:56 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> How does FD work exactly?<br /><br />FD is one of the best spells a Necromancer gets. It will save your @ss more than you can count.<br /><br />UP to lvl 35 mobs it totally wipes their damage table, so when you are feigned, the mob will forget about you and walk away.<br /><br />From lvl 35 (mobs level) the damage table is only cleared partially, the mob will remember you sometimes and reaggro if you stand up. The higher the level of the mob, the more will it remember what you have done to him (and as a good necro, this will be ALOT :D)<br /><br />In Raids you will learn, that FD is very useful for you aggro management. So after some HARD hitting spells, you can FD to get rid of some hate. Use ist and your DPS will increase.<br /><br />One thing with FD and leaving your PC: <br />NEVER leave some lich type spell on your pitiful existence. <br /><br />Hope that helped</span></font></td>
